Creating an accurate supply graph for the streaming market is difficult because calculating the PES is challenging. Streaming companies do not report a clear quantity supplied, as they provide a digital service rather than a tangible product. However, it can be argued that the PES is greater than 1 (elastic). This is because the marginal cost of supplying the service to an additional customer is very low relative to the subscription price. As a result, firms such as Netflix can increase the number of customers served with relatively little increase in costs, which helps explain the viability of lower-priced subscription tiers.

